programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 1996: Steelers vs. Cowboys
programme.desc: From 1996: Pittsburgh vs. Dallas in Super Bowl XXX in Tempe, Ariz. The Cowboys struck early and often to win 27-13, scoring on their first three possessions. Larry Brown intercepted two Pittsburgh passes in the second half. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 1997: Packers vs. Patriots
programme.desc: From 1997: New England vs. Green Bay in Super Bowl XXXI in New Orleans. The Packers topped New England 35-21. Desmond Howard scored on a 99-yard kickoff return and earned MVP honors. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 1998: Broncos vs. Packers
programme.desc: From 1998: Denver vs. Green Bay in Super Bowl XXXII in San Diego. John Elway earned his long-awaited first championship by leading the Broncos to a 31-24 win. Terrell Davis ran for 3 TDs and 157 yards. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 1999: Broncos vs. Falcons
programme.desc: From 1999: Denver vs. Atlanta in Super Bowl XXXIII in Miami. Denver won 34-19 as John Elway threw for 336 yards and a touchdown and ran for another score in his final game before retiring. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 2000: Rams vs. Titans
programme.desc: From 2000: Tennessee vs. St. Louis in Super Bowl XXXIV in Atlanta. The Rams won their first title with a 23-16 win over Tennessee. MVP QB Kurt Warner threw for 414 yards and 2 TDs. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 2001: Ravens vs. Giants
programme.desc: From 2001: Baltimore vs. New York Giants in Super Bowl XXXV in Tampa. The Ravens' defense paved the way for a 34-7 victory. Baltimore allowed just 152 yards, forced five turnovers and had four sacks. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 2002: Rams vs. Patriots
programme.desc: From 2002: New England vs. St. Louis in Super Bowl XXXVI in New Orleans. The Patriots won 20-17 on Adam Vinatieri's 48-yard field goal as time expired. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 2003: Buccaneers vs. Raiders
programme.desc: From 2003: Tampa Bay vs. Oakland in Super Bowl XXXVII in San Diego. The Bucs romped to a 48-21 victory after returning 3 INTs for TDs and recording five sacks. Dwight Smith was named MVP with 2 TDs on INT returns. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 2004: Patriots vs. Panthers
programme.desc: From 2004: New England vs. Carolina in Super Bowl XXXVIII in Houston. The Pats won 32-29 on an Adam Vinatieri field goal with four seconds remaining. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 2005: Eagles vs. Patriots
programme.desc: From 2005: New England vs. Philadelphia in Super Bowl XXXIX in Jacksonville. New England won 24-21 to claim its third championship in four years. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 2006: Steelers vs. Seahawks
programme.desc: From 2006: Pittsburgh vs. Seattle in Super Bowl XL in Detroit. Hines Ward caught five passes for 123 yards and scored a 43-yard TD off a reverse that sealed the Steelers' 21-10 victory. It was the fifth Super Bowl victory for Pittsburgh. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 2007: Colts vs. Bears
programme.desc: From 2007: Indianapolis vs. Chicago in Super Bowl XLI in Miami. RBs Dominic Rhodes and Joseph Addai combined to rush for 190 yards and Kelvin Hayden returned an INT for a TD in the Colts' 29-17 victory. Thomas Jones ran for 112 yards for the Bears. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 2008: Giants vs. Patriots
programme.desc: From 2008: New York Giants vs. New England in Super Bowl XLII. The Giants ended 18-0 New England's quest for a perfect season with a 17-14 upset. The win was sparked by a stellar defensive effort and a long TD drive in the final minutes directed by Eli Manning. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 2009: Cardinals vs. Steelers
programme.desc: From 2009: Arizona vs. Pittsburgh in Super Bowl XLIII. The Steelers won 27-23 for their sixth Super Bowl victory. Santonio Holmes caught the winning TD with 35 seconds remaining. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 2010: Colts vs. Saints
programme.desc: From 2010: Indianapolis vs. New Orleans in Super Bowl XLIV. The Saints overcame an early deficit to win a 31-17 decision. QB Drew Brees completed 32 of 39 passing attempts for the Saints. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 2011: Packers vs. Steelers
programme.desc: From 2011: Green Bay vs. Pittsburgh in Super Bowl XLV. The Packers won 31-25, with Aaron Rodgers throwing 3 TD passes. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 2012: Giants vs. Patriots
programme.desc: From 2012: New York Giants vs. New England in Super Bowl XLVI. The Giants won 21-17, with game MVP Eli Manning engineering a come-from-behind fourth-quarter touchdown drive. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 2013: 49ers vs. Ravens
programme.desc: San Francisco vs. Baltimore in Super Bowl XLVII. The Ravens won 34-31 in New Orleans. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 2014: Broncos vs. Seahawks
programme.desc: Denver vs. Seattle in Super Bowl XLVIII. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: Super Bowl XLIX: New England Patriots vs. Seattle Seahawks
programme.sub-title: Super Bowl XLIX: New England Patriots vs. Seattle Seahawks
programme.desc: New England vs. Seattle in Super Bowl XLIX. Tom Brady led the Patriots comeback, with the win capped by the game-ending interception by Malcolm Butler at the 1-yard line to seal the 28-24 victory. (cc)(n)
